{{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = ISRO Propulsion Complex (IPRC) |nativename = |nativename_a = |nativename_r = |logo = Indian Space Research Organisation Logo.svg |logo_width = 100px |seal = |seal_width = |picture = |picture_width = |picture_caption = |formed = |date1 = |date1_name = |date2 = |date2_name = |preceding1 = |preceding2 = |parent_agency = [[ISRO]] |jurisdiction = [[Government of India|Department of Space]] |headquarters = [[Mahendragiri]] |employees = 600+ |budget = See the budget of [[ISRO]] |chief1_name = T. Mookiah<ref>http://www.iprc.gov.in/</ref> |chief1_position = Director |chief2_name = |chief2_position = |child2_agency = |website = [http://www.iprc.gov.in iprc.gov.in] |footnotes = |map = |map_width = |map_caption = |chief3_name=|chief3_position=|chief4_name=|chief4_position=|chief5_name=|chief5_position=|chief6_name=|chief6_position=|chief7_name=|chief7_position=|chief8_name=|chief8_position=|chief9_name=|chief9_position=|parent_department=}}
The '''ISRO Propulsion Complex''' ('''IPRC'''), located at [[Mahendragiri]] of [[Tamil Nadu]], is an [[Indian Space Research Organisation]] centre involved in testing, assembling, and integrating propulsion systems and stages that are developed at ISRO's [[Liquid Propulsion Systems Centre]]s. Formerly, IPRC was known as LPSC, Mahendragiri, functioning under [[Liquid Propulsion Systems Centre|LPSC]], Valiamala in [[Thiruvananthapuram]] of [[Kerala]]. It was elevated as an independent centre and renamed as IPRC with effect from February 1, 2014.<ref name="ISRO">http://www.isro.gov.in/isrocentres/iprc.aspx</ref><ref>http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/lpsc-at-mahendragiri-elevated/article5641468.ece</ref><ref>http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2014-02-01/science/46897203_1_mahendragiri-vikram-sarabhai-space-centre-gslv</ref>
It is one of the ISRO centres that could be called as the "Jet Propulsion Laboratory of India" as all liquid, [[cryogenic]] and [[semicryogenic]] stage and engine related tests of ISRO's launch vehicles and satellites are carried out here.<ref>http://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/lpsc-mahendragiri-to-function-as-independent-unit-minister-114013100771_1.html</ref>.
==Facilities== Following activities are currently carried out at IPRC:<ref name="ISRO" /> *Assembly, integration and testing of launch vehicle motors and stages *Servicing of launch vehicle motors and stages *Propellant storage *Sea level and high altitude tests of [[Vikas engine|Vikas]], PS2/GS2, PS4, L40, L110, S200, [[CE-7.5]] and [[CE-20]] cryogenic engines, and steering engines<ref>http://www.frontline.in/cover-story/gslvlinked-facilities/article5596658.ece</ref> *L40 and CE-7.5 development and qualification tests *Assembly and integration of flight stages PS2/GS2, PS4, L40 for [[PSLV]] and [[GSLV]] missions *Assembly and integration of [[Apogee kick motor|LAM]] engine and [[Attitude control|AOCS]] thruster for satellites
