A '''pin lichen''', or '''calicoid lichen''', is a [[crustose lichen|crustose]] [[lichen]] with small fruiting bodies pointing up that look like a [[dressmaker]]'s pin''.<ref name=LYP>Sharon Eversman, [http://www.nps.gov/yell/planyourvisit/upload/YS15(3)partII.pdf "Lichens in Yellowstone Park"], Plan Your Visit, National Park Service</ref> It includes members of the lichen [[genera]] ''[[Calicium]]'' and ''[[Chaenotheca]]''.<ref name=SSFGCL>Field Guide to California Lichens, Stephen Sharnoff, Yale University Press, 2014, {{ISBN|978-0-300-19500-2}}</ref>{{rp|15}}

